    "story": "Two Gallants",
    "name": "Donnybrook Tram Line",
    "kind": "route",
    "gloss": "Corley and the maid would have taken this line as they navigated to and from Donnybrook.",
    "quote": "[Lenehan] watched Corley's head which turned at every moment towards the young woman's face like a big ball revolving on a pivot. He kept the pair in view until he had seen them climbing the stairs of the Donnybrook tram; then he turned about and went back the way he had come.",
    "srcText": "climbing the stairs of the Donnybrook tram",
    "essay": "https://mappingdubliners.org/donnybrook-tramline/",
    "source": "own"
   },
